OL,3,CCalls for kettle prison ban after
OL,4,CSouthport killer alleged attack
OL,6,F"So I ask the minister, when will it
OL,7,Fconclude? Why hasn't every prison
OL,8,Fofficer exposed to dangerous inmates
OL,9,Falready been provided with a stab
OL,10,Fvest? Not in June, but now today.
OL,12,F"I have spoken to officers who say
OL,13,Fattacks with boiling water are not
OL,14,Funcommon. Will he commit today to
OL,15,Forder the removal of every kettle from
OL,16,Fhigh-risk prisoners? Not in June, but
OL,17,Fnow, today. This goes deeper than one
OL,18,Freview, men like Rudakubana and Abedi
OL,19,Fglorify violence, they dream of
OL,20,Fmartyrdom, and, still, governors
OL,21,Fpander to them.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
