OL,3,CCalls for kettle prison ban after
OL,4,CSouthport killer alleged attack
OL,6,F"All prisons carry out regular risk
OL,7,Fassessments and implemented associated
OL,8,Fsafe systems of work. If a risk is
OL,9,Fidentified regarding kettle-use or
OL,10,Fintelligence is received that one
OL,11,Fmight be used in assault, the kettle
OL,12,Fwill be withdrawn.
OL,14,F"And, frankly, for 14 years kettles
OL,15,Fwere used under the previous
OL,16,Fgovernment's watch... they rightly
OL,17,Ftrusted the professional skill and
OL,18,Fexpertise of those running our prisons
OL,19,Fand working in our prisons, and that's
OL,20,Fwhat we are doing now."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU|D@WO]
